The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Garberville had a population of 818. The population density was {{convert|305.2|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Garberville was 646 (79.0%) [[White Americans|White]], 2 (0.2%) [[African Americans|African American]], 21 (2.6%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 22 (2.7%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 2 (0.2%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 33 (4.0%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 92 (11.2%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 85 persons (10.4%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Garberville CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0628154 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The census reported that 96.8% of the population lived in households, 2.3% lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0.9% were institutionalized.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 396 households, out of which 59 (14.9%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 104 (26.3%) were married-couple households, 31 (7.8%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 131 (33.1%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 130 (32.8%) had a male householder with no partner present. 196 households (49.5%) were one person, and 81 (20.5%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.00.<ref name=DP1/> There were 165 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (41.7% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Garberville CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0628154 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 21, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 135 people (16.5%) under the age of 18, 47 people (5.7%) aged 18 to 24, 250 people (30.6%) aged 25 to 44, 205 people (25.1%) aged 45 to 64, and 181 people (22.1%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 43.4{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 99.0 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 456 housing units at an average density of {{convert|170.1|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 396 (86.8%) were occupied. Of these, 212 (53.5%) were owner-occupied, and 184 (46.5%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

